<!--
  NuGet Package Validation (ApiCompat) baseline suppression for ProcessKit.Testing.

  WHAT is suppressed: exactly the CassetteEntry generated positional constructor, on BOTH target
  frameworks (net8.0 + net10.0). Diagnostic CP0002 = "a member present in the baseline (2.4.2) is
  absent in the current build": the F# record `ProcessKit.Testing.CassetteEntry` had its positional
  constructor's arity change when the PTY-cassette fields `Pty` / `PtyCols` / `PtyRows` and later the
  `Signalled` marker were added in [Unreleased] (cassette formats v4 and v6 — see
  src/ProcessKit.Testing/Cassette.fs). Adding a field to an F# positional record replaces its
  15-argument constructor with a 19-argument one, so ApiCompat
  correctly reports the old-arity constructor as removed relative to the last published release.

  WHY this specific break is allowed (a deliberate, narrow, documented exception — NOT a major bump,
  NOT a field removal; the accumulated [Unreleased] release stays a minor):
    1. `CassetteEntry` is a documented SERIALIZATION DTO, not a stable construction contract. Its own
       doc comment says to "inspect a cassette file directly rather than depending on this shape"; it
       is public only so System.Text.Json can (de)serialize it.
    2. Real consumption is deserialization through the parameterless `[<CLIMutable>]` constructor +
       property setters, which field additions do NOT break: old cassettes still load and the new
       fields default (documented v1->v6 back-compat — a pre-v4 entry keys as a non-PTY run and a
       pre-v6 entry without a signal remains unobserved).
    3. Fields were already added to `CassetteEntry` in earlier minor releases (`StdoutBase64`,
       `EnvFingerprint`) the same non-breaking way.

  INVARIANT — keep this suppression NARROW. It lists ONLY the CassetteEntry constructor. Removing or
  renaming ANY OTHER public member (in ProcessKit.Testing or any other package) must still fail
  `dotnet pack` under package validation; this is not a blanket suppression, and no other package
  carries a suppression file. When the next MAJOR version is cut, bump
  PackageValidationBaselineVersion (Directory.Build.props) to the new baseline and DELETE this file so
  the arity change is absorbed into the new major line (see ROADMAP.md "Versioning & stability").
-->
<Suppressions xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema">
  <Suppression>
    <DiagnosticId>CP0002</DiagnosticId>
    <Target>M:ProcessKit.Testing.CassetteEntry.#ctor(System.String,System.String[],System.String,System.String,System.Boolean,System.String[],System.String,System.String,System.String,System.String,System.Nullable{System.Int32},System.Boolean,System.Nullable{System.Int32},System.Boolean,System.Double)</Target>
    <Left>lib/net10.0/ProcessKit.Testing.dll</Left>
    <Right>lib/net10.0/ProcessKit.Testing.dll</Right>
    <IsBaselineSuppression>true</IsBaselineSuppression>
  </Suppression>
  <Suppression>
    <DiagnosticId>CP0002</DiagnosticId>
    <Target>M:ProcessKit.Testing.CassetteEntry.#ctor(System.String,System.String[],System.String,System.String,System.Boolean,System.String[],System.String,System.String,System.String,System.String,System.Nullable{System.Int32},System.Boolean,System.Nullable{System.Int32},System.Boolean,System.Double)</Target>
    <Left>lib/net8.0/ProcessKit.Testing.dll</Left>
    <Right>lib/net8.0/ProcessKit.Testing.dll</Right>
    <IsBaselineSuppression>true</IsBaselineSuppression>
  </Suppression>
</Suppressions>
